type":"string"},{"id":"efd88ecf-f334-48f3-a581-33c7ec591392","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"ad282fac-fe02-49d9-acdf-3b5281990205","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4914,1420],"id":"467714b4-ac1e-4f8f-947e-0e2c983c95b7","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"subject":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage ","bodyContent":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","toRecipients":"={{ $json.email || 'ops@company.com' }}","additionalFields":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook","typeVersion":2,"position":[5238,1420],"id":"6b0f4730-abc2-4c8a-bdbf-fa8add1ebc7b","name":"Escalate Failure to Outlook","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Job Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5562,1420],"id":"5e783f84-8b72-4f0d-8ae3-55f5802f2da1","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf06158-job`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Fetch Current Metrics","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"c6d512af-074c-7a5a-1a00-435605525b8c","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fetch Current Metrics\n\nGET https://api.example.com/v1/jobs — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Severity Signals · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"941cc1e3-5ef9-a031-9bc2-e8a960d56b9e","name":"Note: Fetch Current Metrics"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Severity Signals\n\nCustom JavaScript: Score each job 0-100 from simple heuristics\n\nNext: Grade Severity Tier","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"fc5a72c7-364f-9ee1-fdd9-f7536a70b4e8","name":"Note: Compute Severity Signals"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Grade Severity Tier\n\nRoutes each item to one of 4 lanes: info, warning, critical + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Just Record (Info) · ②→ Warn Channel (Slack) · ③→ Page Urgently (Outlook) · ④→ Archive Unscored","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"0b3ef462-4212-a188-8b07-ac1c1051c109","name":"Note: Grade Severity Tier"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Just Record (Info)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Job Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,40],"id":"170c40f2-95e7-fe6d-9d2d-f90a460f9ec9","name":"Note: Just Record (Info)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Warn Channel (Slack)\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#automation`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"67e92e0d-27cc-8bec-c876-b0ccf6afe897","name":"Note: Warn Channel (Slack)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page Urgently (Outlook)\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1000],"id":"cf571595-fce2-3b58-5d5c-feb72a518492","name":"Note: Page Urgently (Outlook)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Unscored\n\nAppends a new row to 'Job Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,1480],"id":"46d0b310-783f-be6f-5acd-1c367a57e1d9","name":"Note: Archive Unscored"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Tier Outcomes\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"522ed0bf-6d2f-d582-03a9-3e020c48c6ce","name":"Note: Merge Tier Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"afd129c4-bbd2-4878-03cb-0f36f4209375","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"08cd2fb3-ed64-df05-a729-91f990280797","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"2d553324-6652-102c-274b-b61575e1ec04","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"bbbc8ddd-9352-52c9-7237-10cbb85ae56c","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"a9b07014-12a4-2443-62dd-2a546f65dc0b","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Job Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"8f69aa6c-b662-2ed5-3dfa-af57e936facf","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#automation`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"c3e2bff8-c235-b95f-3d06-d0daf359c280","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Outlook","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"6a1a90a0-deb2-2482-3198-55f15913973e","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Outlook\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,1540],"id":"44c59b44-0cf6-a247-a2ff-a0dc55bf7e6f","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Outlook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nAppends a new row to 'Job Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,1540],"id":"dac57f61-22fb-75cf-e849-dffb1237e19e","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Notify stakeholders on changes with Outlook hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Event Notification · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nNotify stakeholders on changes with Outlook hands-free. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual integrations is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Fetch Current Metrics → Compute Severity Signals → Grade Severity Tier → Just Record (Info) → Merge Tier Outcomes → Enrich with Reference Data → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to event notification without manual effort\n- Anyone automating integrations in productivity\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"4ef211ed-e3f8-e697-c7a9-fae00e164da2","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThree response tiers, not a single yes/no alert, match the response to the severity — logging every metric quietly would bury the one critical spike, and paging on-call for every info-level blip trains them to ignore alerts entirely. Critical gets a distinct, louder channel from warning on purpose.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"2a6fa7c2-d583-1f08-288b-cc50bba88598","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAlready production-grade — deepen your understanding:\n\n1. Adjust the tier thresholds and see how alert sensitivity changes.\n2. Trigger a critical-tier value and confirm it pages a different channel than warning does.\n3. Add a 4th tier between warning and critical.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"e675ef48-c302-0d08-2ded-8c76d5b8280f","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"a96d015a-a921-9ad0-c0b3-557b7f9159e2","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"b7da02f1-a25f-9ded-baf9-c599a8214299","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your integrations process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"d49cf875-a8df-f0c8-5dd6-54d7935ae908","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Fetch Current Metrics","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fetch Current 